This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and language generation, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed approach, which is evaluated using metrics such as perplexity and BLEU, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of a corpus to build the models, which falls under the category of data science (cs.SD).
